<subSubSection id="C36204A9986F7073C5F8FF40FE21FE95" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BC75722986F7073C5F8FF40FE21FE95" blockId="60.[136,1452,158,508]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30986F7073C5F8FF40FE37FF6C" bold="true" box="[189,485,194,220]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Ecology and distribution</emphasis>
: This species is found growing on exposed branches of trees and bushes in rainforests, asociated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1986F7073C46BFF65FE74FEB0" box="[302,422,230,256]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dictyota">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30986F7073C46BFF65FE74FEB0" box="[302,422,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">R. dictyota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1986F7073C49FFF65FD98FEB0" baseAuthorityName="Krog &amp; Swinscow" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[474,586,230,256]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pusiola">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30986F7073C49FFF65FD98FEB0" box="[474,586,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">R. pusiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<quantity id="4C80FAC7986F7073C72FFF64FD2BFEB1" box="[618,761,230,257]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="1400.0" valueMin="900.0">900–1400 m</quantity>
. It is known from 
<collectingCountry id="F36F17B2986F7073C6FBFF64FBFAFEB0" box="[958,1064,230,256]" name="Australia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36F17B2986F7073C177FF65FB33FEB0" box="[1074,1249,230,257]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, Timor (
<collectingCountry id="F36F17B2986F7073C078FF64FA76FEB1" box="[1341,1444,230,257]" name="Tanzania" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Zanzibar</collectingCountry>
) and South America (
<collectingCountry id="F36F17B2986F7073C428FE88FE35FE95" box="[365,487,266,293]" name="Venezuela" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36204A9986F7073C5F8FEACFF3DFE4C" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC75722986F7073C5F8FEACFAC1FE20" blockId="60.[136,1452,158,508]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30986F7073C5F8FEACFEF8FEF8" bold="true" box="[189,298,302,328]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Remarks</emphasis>
: In northern South America this varieties is only known from the Venezuelan Andes (
<figureCitation id="13434BA7986F7073C05AFEACFAB5FEF9" box="[1311,1383,302,329]" captionStart="FIGURES 4– 5" captionStartId="9.[136,243,1990,2012]" captionTargetBox="[292,1304,206,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[278,1309,190,1966]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4– 5. Upper surface of R. venezuelensis showing pseudocyphellae as observed by SEM. 14. Lateral pseudocyphellae and small pore-like structures, scale = 15 mm. 15. Lateral pseudocyphellae, scale = 30.5 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5425202/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The morphological and chemical characters of this varieties have been described in detail by Morales &amp; Marcano (1994). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE92AD3986F7073C5CDFEF4FEE3FE20" author="Stevens, G. N." box="[136,305,374,400]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="107 - 223" refId="ref53773" refString="Stevens, G. N. (1987) The lichen genus Ramalina in Australia. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany Series 16: 107 - 223." type="book chapter" year="1987">Stevens (1987)</bibRefCitation>
reported the presence of minor quantities of paludosic acid in specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F36F17B2986F7073C1E0FEF4FADDFE20" box="[1189,1295,374,400]" name="Australia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
